book_title: The Future Use of Legume Nodulating Bacteria (LNB) In Indonesia Technical and Economic Perspectives
title: Economic Potentials of Legume Crops in Plantation Management
abstract: Legume crops are commonly used for special purposes in plantation management such as for shading, support tree, windbreaker, and cover crops. Besides its main functions as complement plant, legume has another benefit for maintaining soil fertility and productivity. The leguminous plants are very common in plantation management because their capacity to produce root nodule.
